  "text": "• Selective Initialization: Yang [CITATION_1] presented a selective initial population technique based on the K-nearest neighbor (KNN) sub graph. The KNN builds a graph contains all cities such as c i and c j , based on the distance matrix. Where c i is one of the KNN cities of c j or c j is one of the KNN cities of c i . The selective initial population technique grants the higher priority to the KNN sub graph edges. Firstly, from the city c, the next city will be randomly selected from c's KNN list, but if all cities of c in KNN list are selected, then the next city is randomly selected from unvisited cities.",
